title: Co-founder & CEO
summary:
Currently, I am the co-founder and CEO of Remuner, the variable compensation platform that helps companies align their goals and incentives with their employees by automating all aspects of sales commission plans. At Remuner, I lead the vision, strategy, and execution of the product, as well as the fundraising, business development, sales and team building. I leverage my expertise in AI, data, operations and sales to deliver a modern commission management platform that enables data-driven decisions, maximizes performance, and motivates and retains the best talent. I also collaborate as Venture Partner at Antai Ventures, where I support the next generation of founders in building and launching their products to the market. I am passionate about creating and scaling ventures that make a positive impact and I am always looking for new opportunities and challenges.

I am a serial entrepreneur with over 10 years of experience in creating and scaling ventures that solve real problems and add value to customers and society. I have co-founded and exited three companies whose products are used by millions of users every month and invested in other promising startups as a Business Angel.

title: Co-Founder
summary:
A typical Njord client has complexities in the deal making such as…
Cross hierarchical decision making on the customer side (often higher up than most people realise)
Cross functional decision making
A complex offering that takes a long time for new people to handle on their own
The environment on the customer side is a blend of processes and interfacing technologies

These 4 complexities lead to another key trait of our clients, which is a very high dependency on key people in the deal making. Often a CEO, a CTO and a Head of sales. We call it the rainmaker dependency. Hiring more and more sales people only makes the matter worse as your rainmakers have to hold the new sales peoples’ hands, which they don't have time for. We often see companies making the mistake of recruiting too many new sales people and then ending up in the calendar problem. They find themselves having to support everyone else and then experiencing lower sales as a consequence.

Most of our clients aim at becoming the leader in their category and in their core customer segment. It is also quite common that a Njord client is trying to establish or grow a new solution category which has its own list of challenges and special moves.

Looking forward to talking more about your exciting potential to dominate your finite market and category.

title: Chairperson
summary:
CEO @ Njord 

Scaling rainmakers is a leverage problem.

When we built Njord, we started with the customer and worked backwards. How do the world’s leading companies actually run their most important, high-stakes deals. The answer was. They use 14 to 18 disconnected systems and several full-time specialists just to manage the motion. The tech stack alone costs about €19k per month. It works, but only for the biggest enterprises.

Most companies will never get access to that level of capability. 
And that felt fundamentally wrong.

So we built Njord to change this.
It gives every rainmaker the power of a Fortune 500 deal room at less than 10 percent of the cost.

Small teams win bigger deals.
Challengers compete with giants.
And rainmakers finally get the platform they always should have had.

————————————————————————————
As an angel investor and board member, I also 
support and mentor promising tech companies such as Qurator, a decarbonization ecosystem, and Venizum, a translation system connector. I have co-founded several successful ventures, such as Arctic Group, Djava Factory, Arctiquator, and WorqApp, and have extensive experience in working with and expanding to over 50 countries, mainly in EMEA and APAC. I’m also the creator of the High Impact Management

title: Co-Founder & COO
summary:
Build Concierge is your AI powered omnichannel customer engagement platform that converts, automates and scales. 24/7. Always on. Always human.

Businesses today face growing complexity: rising volumes of enquiries, disjointed systems, and manual processes that slow teams down and limit growth. Opportunities are missed. Customers wait. Efficiency suffers. 

Our all-in-one platform is designed to streamline operations, improve responsiveness, and scale effortlessly. 

From calls and chats to WhatsApp, SMS, emails, and appointments, it handles every interaction in real time. It understands intent, responds instantly, and follows up automatically. 

It integrates seamlessly into your existing systems and workflows such as CRM, job management and scheduling tools, so you don’t need to change how you work to benefit from automation.

No more missed steps. No more resource drain. Just intelligent automation built around how your business really works and where it’s going. 

Built for scale. Powered by AI.

title: Founder Chairman and CEO
summary:
Born in the UK and now living in Israel, I have always been driven by innovation and execution. My entrepreneurial journey began early, starting a printing business as a teenager, followed by a career defined by resilience, determination, and building category-defining companies, despite personal challenges including dyslexia and hearing loss.

After transitioning into technology in 1998, following a decade building speciality bakery businesses in New York and Leeds, I founded Masternaut at the age of 40. Masternaut pioneered web-based vehicle tracking in the UK and, under my leadership, grew to become Europe’s largest fleet management service. The business was sold for $80m in 2011 and is today owned by Michelin, the world-famous tyre and mobility business.

In 2013, I founded BigChange, a mobile workforce management platform that transformed how field service businesses operate. Over the following eight years, BigChange became a market-leading technology company and was awarded the Queen’s Award for Enterprise. In 2021, Boston-based Great Hill Partners invested $100m, valuing the company at $135m. In 2024, BigChange was acquired by Simpro Group, backed by K1, at an enterprise value exceeding $450m.

My current venture, Build Concierge, valued at $50m, is an omnichannel customer engagement platform built for the entire service industry. We have distilled decades of operational and technology experience into a new AI-enabled SaaS platform that automates time-consuming processes, connects fragmented systems, and raises customer service standards.
With Build Concierge, companies never miss a call or a message. Every customer interaction across voice, email, SMS, WhatsApp, webchat, and social media is captured, structured, and converted into actionable insight.

Our AI Concierge Advisors operate 24/7, delivering the right information at the right time across text, image, and video, augmenting existing teams rather than replacing them. The result is consistent, high-quality customer engagement at scale.

Alongside building businesses, I actively support the entrepreneurial ecosystem as an angel investor. My investments include Handshaik, Rated People, Panintelligence, Electron Green, and StoriBoard.

I am also a committed philanthropist, supporting local communities and charitable causes through my registered charity, the Amanda and Martin Port Foundation.

titleDescription:
Enabling wealth managers, advisers & investment platforms to complete their proposition with investment backed loans from £25k without the need to move custody, source the capital, handle the administration or manage the compliance requirements.

Lombard loans have historically only available to clients with more than £1m and, even then, for advisors, non-bank wealth managers & investment platforms, they have to move the assets to a private banks custody - Firenze is changing all that.

Firenze provides a seamlessly integrated loan platform that takes care of the technology for application, underwriting & monitoring, handles the consumer credit compliance & provides the capital to allow you to offer loans to your clients from as little as £25k.

Helping investors meet their liquidity needs, grow their wealth or have more flexible tax planning.

title: Vice President of Sales
summary:
As Founding VP of Sales at Lleverage, I’m leading our GTM strategy and building the commercial foundation of one of Europe’s most promising AI-native platforms.

Lleverage helps companies automate repetitive, manual business processes using practical, real-world AI. Think: processing purchase orders, handling logistics emails, generating reports — tasks that eat up time and create inefficiencies. With Lleverage, these workflows become intelligent, automated, and scalable — without the need for complex integrations or internal AI expertise.

Backed by top-tier investors (€5M in (pre-)seed) and growing fast, we’re already delivering measurable value to operationally complex businesses — helping them save time, reduce costs, and scale smarter.

Before Lleverage, I worked as Founding VP of Sales at Workwize, where I built and led the GTM-team and commercial strategy for our B2B SaaS platform — supporting companies across the globe in managing the full lifecycle of IT hardware for remote and hybrid teams. In my role I led the company towards a €13M Series A funding, led by Klass Capital in December 2024.

With 10+ years of experience in B2B SaaS, including as Managing Director at Meltwater with full P&L responsibility, I’ve led teams, driven international expansion, and consistently delivered double-digit growth across Europe and the US.

I hold a Master of Law from the University of Amsterdam and a certificate in Consumer Behavior from the London School of Economics. My core competencies include develop, setting up and execute on GTM strategy, sales strategy, and leading by example. I am passionate about SaaS, AI & Tech (innovations), accelerating revenue, people development and making a positive impact while scaling organizations.
titleDescription:
Lleverage is a B2B AI platform that helps companies automate repetitive, manual business processes — from data entry to document handling — using powerful, real-world AI.

Our platform empowers teams to turn inefficient workflows into intelligent automation flows in just minutes, without the need for complex integrations or internal AI expertise. Whether it’s processing purchase orders, handling logistics emails, or generating custom reports — Lleverage delivers time savings, cost reduction, and consistency at scale.

We’re already helping leading manufacturers and wholesalers streamline operations, boost productivity, and free up their teams to focus on high-impact work.

Backed by top-tier investors, Lleverage is one of the fastest-growing AI-native platforms in Europe — building toward a future where businesses scale not with headcount, but with intelligence. We have successfully secured €5M in our (pre-)seed round so far.

summary:
With a robust background that spans over a decade in management consulting & entrepreneurship, my journey has led me to co-found Karomia. Here, our mission is to simplify Double Materiality assessments, supporting organizations striving to report under the CSRD and align with ESRS. My expertise in data analysis and commitment to sustainability drives the company's mission, as we work to foster transparency and accountability in corporate reporting.

At Karomia, we have developed a software solution that revolutionizes how companies approach their sustainability reporting. Leveraging my data analysis skills and deep understanding of management consulting, my team and I support businesses eager to comply with evolving regulations. Our dedication to making CSRD reporting straightforward reflects my passion for innovation and my belief in the power of technology to create a more sustainable and responsible corporate landscape.
titleDescription:
Struggling to build with your ESG report? 

Our software makes ESG reporting simple! 
We support companies who want to report, in line with ESRS or VSME standards. 

What you can expect from our ESG reporting module:
1️⃣ dump (or upload rather) any documents or files that might contain relevant ESG info

title: CEO and Co-Founder
summary:
"The real secret of success is enthusiasm." – Walter Chrysler

Co-founder and CEO of Sulapac, an internationally awarded material innovation company with the mission to save the world from plastic waste. Sulapac helps brands across industries to replace conventional plastics with a sustainable alternative that doesn’t compromise functionality or aesthetics. 

Together with our customers and partners Sulapac has a crucial role in accelerating the plastic waste-free future and the change towards a circular economy. Succeeding takes boldness, ambition and determination, and this is what team Sulapac is all about. However, to ultimately accomplish the mission, a set of solutions is needed: We must take an interdisciplinary approach and collaborate across industries and sectors, globally.


Before founding Sulapac with my colleague PhD Laura Tirkkonen-Rajasalo and Antti Pärssinen, I worked in leadership positions for 10 years at universities in Finland and The Netherlands. I’m specialized in medical biomaterials and have supervised 7 PhD theses, 14 Master’s theses and 5 Bachelor’s theses. Science is always close to my heart, and the backbone of Sulapac.

summary:
I’m a growth-driven business leader passionate about building bridges between technology, commerce, and global customer experiences. Over the past years, I’ve helped leading fintech and payment companies expand across Europe and LATAM, driving scalable growth strategies and long-term partnerships.

At STAMP, I lead growth and expansion across European markets — shaping how travelers and retailers connect through a truly modern ecosystem that blends Real TaxFree Shopping and Alternative Payments & Engagement Platforms (WeChat Pay, Alipay, and more).
My focus is on defining GTM strategies, building high-performing teams, and designing data-driven systems that accelerate merchant adoption and retention.

Before STAMP, I contributed to the international growth of Trustly, SlimPay, and Paysafe, leading enterprise sales, open banking launches, and cross-regional business development initiatives.

I’m passionate about scaling innovative products, optimizing full-funnel growth processes, and forging strategic partnerships that create tangible impact.
Driven by innovation and purpose, I aim to redefine how global commerce operates — making it smarter, more connected, and more sustainable.
titleDescription:
Driven by innovation and purpose, STAMP is redefining global commerce through technology — creating a smarter, more connected, and transparent way for travelers to shop across Europe.
At its core, STAMP empowers merchants and international shoppers through two complementary solutions:
- Real TaxFree, a modern system that enables instant VAT savings at checkout — simplifying the entire tax-free process from purchase to customs validation.
- Alternative Payments by STAMP, a global payments and engagement platform that connects European retailers with international consumers through WeChat Pay, Alipay, and other leading digital wallets.

Together, these innovations transform Travel Retail into a seamless, data-driven ecosystem where every transaction builds trust, loyalty, and growth.

🧭 Expert in defining and executing GTM strategies in fast-paced, high-growth environments
💼 Lead regional teams across Sales, Operations and Growth Marketing
🤝 Strong in strategic partnerships, enterprise sales, and long-term merchant relationships
🔗 Bridge between local markets and global Product, Tech, and Marketing teams
📈  Experience in launching and scaling tech products across Italy, Spain & Portugal
🔄 Data-driven and automation-focused approach to revenue growth
⚙️ Skilled in building scalable systems and streamlining full-funnel sales processes
🚀 Passionate about product-led growth and driving merchant success from onboarding to expansion

title: CEO
summary:
I’m the CEO of STAMP — the Real Tax Free solution that helps merchants boost in-store sales by offering international shoppers an instant deferral of VAT payment before checkout.
No queues. No paperwork. No delays. Just higher conversion at the point of sale.

Since 2009, I’ve been deep in the tax-free industry — first at Global Blue, then as founder of Woonivers. Both acted as intermediaries in the refund process.

With STAMP, we’re doing things differently: we build the technology that empowers merchants to serve global shoppers directly, using AI, data, and embedded finance to drive seamless, real-time results.

Since 2018, I’ve been fully focused on innovation and technology — not just as an entrepreneur, but also as a lecturer at leading institutions like ESADE (FT Top 10 Executive Education) and IED, Italy’s reference for fashion and innovation.

To make all this possible, I build teams from scratch — because innovation and disruption don’t come from code alone. They come from humans creating together with purpose.

🌍 ESADE & IESE Alumni | 💡 BCorp Advocate | 🧠 Donkey-minded, Unicorn-hearted

The world needs both Unicorns and Donkeys.

title: Founder & CEO
summary:
Road transport is the one of the biggest carbon problems. But I'm convinced that for the modern fleet, electrification isn't just a green initiative; it's a strategic investment that delivers tangible returns.

When we started Rightcharge, the challenge was clear. The transition to EVs was being held back by fragmentation and complexity. Good people in fleet, finance, and HR were spending their days buried in spreadsheets or mopping up after existing fuel systems that weren’t built for EV, trying to make it work.

We believe choosing and managing sustainable transport should be effortless. That’s why we’re building the revenue engine behind sustainable business growth for our customers.

We exist to make the selling and adoption of clean transport easier. We do this by providing one unified platform that turns the chaos of charging payments into a simple, automated system.

With Rightcharge, you can: 
✅ Access over 70% of the UK’s public charging network.
✅ Pay drivers the precise cost for home charging, automatically and without admin. 
✅ Get a single, HMRC-compliant bill for all home, public, and workplace charging. 
✅ Prevent fraud with technology that links charging sessions to specific work vehicles. 
✅ Gain strategic insights on costs and carbon to track your ESG goals.

An EV bought today gets cleaner every year, just by plugging in. Our mission is to make that process as simple and scalable as possible.

Fleets using Rightcharge are now confidently reimbursing their employees, cutting costs by up to 90% and carbon by 30%, while eliminating the risk of fraud. The result is that businesses are transitioning their vehicles to EVs faster than ever before.

If you're leading a fleet through its transition to electric, I'd love to connect.

title: Founder & CEO
summary:
At INXY Payments, we build the financial rails that connect traditional Web2 businesses with modern digital asset infrastructure.

We operate as a licensed fintech across multiple jurisdictions (EU + Canada) and process over $3B+ in yearly stablecoin payment volume — helping companies accept stablecoin payments, run global mass payouts, and manage seamless stablecoin–fiat conversions.

Beyond merchant payments, we also provide our stablecoin payment infrastructure to other fintechs — including EMI/PI/PSP providers and banks — enabling them to offer compliant stablecoin deposits, payouts, and on/off-ramp capabilities to their own customers.

I focus on designing and scaling financial infrastructure that solves real business problems.
INXY has grown rapidly to $3B+ annual volume, secured VC funding, and obtained regulatory approvals across multiple regions, while powering payment flows for companies across fintech, SaaS, adtech, and digital services.

title: CEO & Founder
summary:
I operate at the intersection of technology, capital, and real-world systems—building platforms that transform how industries work.

Over the past two decades, I’ve been part of several defining waves in global technology and value creation:

• The mobile revolution, when software first became truly global and scaled across continents.
• The emergence of European venture capital as a global force—I entered the industry in 2010, when VC in Europe was still fragmented and unproven. Over the following decade, I helped build one of the first globally-scaling investment platforms, developing strategies, leading investments across Europe, China, India, Israel, and the US, and proving that Europe could originate category-defining technology companies.

Today, I’m focused on the next frontier: where AI meets the physical economy. I’m applying everything I’ve learned about platforms, capital, and technology adoption to reinvent industrial procurement and support the decarbonization of heavy industry.

My core belief: lasting impact is created when three forces align—technology that changes what’s possible, capital that scales it, and operators who execute with clarity and discipline.

I continue to invest selectively in founders and technologies that can reshape essential industries. The next era of wealth creation will be built on intelligent systems that transform the real economy.

title: CEO & Co-Founder
summary:
Digicust offers pre-customs software with integrated AI-based customs assistants. The AI-based customs assistants are trained by customs specialists using the Digicust platform to write customs declarations and assign tariff numbers. From unstructured, incorrect and missing data, the application creates a cycle of qualitative, machine-readable information to automate customs clearance. 

The startup is already processing 150,000 customs declarations per year and supports any company interested in customs automation, such as customs agents, freight forwarders, industrial and trading companies worldwide. Due to the large number of customs cases already processed, Digicust offers an out-of-the-box automation level of between 70 and 90%. In combination with Digicust no-code automation and your customs software, be it AEB, Dakosy, dbh or any other customs solution, you can quickly and easily implement fully automated customs declarations. 

Our mission is to digitize the customs industry in a globally scalable and sustainable way, striving for hyper-automation that significantly improves the current supply chain in terms of speed, efficiency and security.
titleDescription:
Digicust - Scalable Digitalization and Trustworthy AI for Customs Clearance of Tomorrow (www.digicust.com)

Digicust provides a set of virtual customs robots integrated into an AI-based pre-customs software "Digital Customs". These robots learn from customs specialists and officers to perform customs clearance. 

The first virtual customs robot Dexter IDP automatically fills out customs declarations with unstructured and structured data, based on API's, artificial intelligence, intelligent document processing and its machine customs know-how. 

Digicust's mission is to scalably and sustainably digitalize the customs industry globally, aspiring to hyper-automation; tremendously improving the current supply chain in speed, efficiency, and safety.

The vision of this startup is to overcome deep learning stability issues, its black box behavior, including its inability to learn from few samples, and the requirement of large, qualitative data sets to achieve high confidence measures. With these deep-tech innovations, Digicust aims to gradually automate the whole customs clearance process from: 

- creating forgery-proof customs documents, besides the fill-out of customs forms (virtual robots Dexter & Chuck), 
- controlling/requesting missing/right documents (virtual robot Neo), 
- over customs code classification (virtual robot Taric), 
- up to 24/7 self-running customs clearance (virtual robots working together and being integrated in the AI-based pre-customs software Digital Customs). 

With the Digicust IT ecosystem, it is possible to introduce the Internet of Customs, providing cutting-edge use cases for technologies such as Next Generation AI, Digital Twins, Quantum Computing and 5G resulting in the next customs revolution, 24/7 machine customs clearance, and supply chains with enormous speed increase and improved fraud detection.

Key Team: Matthias Pfeiler, Dr. Tech. Ahmad Haj Mosa, Manuel Strausz, Thomas Übellacker, Michael Lisci, BA, Dr. Mouhannad Ali and me

title: Co-Founder & CEO
summary:
KI - in kleinen Schritte, pragmatisch, schnell.
Dafür stehe ich mit meinem jungen Scaleup OMMM.
Aus der Praxis für die Praxis. Echter technologischer Fortschritt, entwickelt in Deutschland, um Industriestandorte in Deutschland zu sichern.

OMMM implementiert bei ihren Kunden eine KI-basierte Software für das Operations Management mit dem Fokus Lebensmittelindustrie, FMCG und Sortenfertigung. Unsere Softwaremodule um den Kern Produktionsplanung herum bauen auf über 25 Jahre Spitzenforschung von Prof. Dr. Horst Tempelmeier an der Uni Köln auf. Weniger als 15 Monate ROI sind Benchmark.

Meine Kernthemen sind der übergreifende Aufbau des Unternehmens, von Strategie bis Vertrieb und Marketing. Hierbei baue ich auf 25 Jahre globale Erfahrung in Wachstum und Transformation auf, gleichzeitig lerne ich jeden Tag so viel Neues im Bereich Software und Operations Management.
titleDescription:
KÜNSTLICHE INTELLIGENZ FÜR IHR OPERATIONS MANAGEMENT
Eine optimale Planung war schon immer essentiell für erfolgreiche industrielle Produktion. Und unmöglich. Denn industrielle Planung ist so vielen Restriktionen und Abhängigkeiten unterworfen, dass sie zu komplex ist, um von menschlicher Intelligenz allein gelöst zu werden.

OMMM setzt auf künstliche Intelligenz und schafft so das bisher Unmögliche: Wir geben Planern echte Kontrolle über industrielle Produktionsplanung.

DIE OMMM PLANUNGS­SUITE
OMMM bietet vier Planungsmodule, welche unabhängig voneinander oder gemeinsam eingesetzt werden können, um allen planerischen Herausforderungen zu begegnen.

NAHTLOSE IT-INTEGRATION
OMMM ist als Cloud- oder On-Premise-Lösung implementierbar. Unabhängig vom existierenden ERP-System fügt sich OMMM mühelos in ihre bestehende IT-Landschaft ein, ohne eine datenführende Rolle zu beanspruchen.

Für das gängige ERP-System von SAP ist OMMM beispielsweise zertifiziert und ermöglicht durch SAP R/3, sowie SAP 4/HANA-Readiness eine nahtlose Migration.

OMMM FÜR ALLE
Innovativ und digital in eine transparente Zukunft: Wir machen ihre Planungskomplexität greifbar und schaffen Mehrwert - sowohl für die strategische als auch die operative Dimension ihrer Supply Chain.

DER OMMM-ALGORITHMUS BASIERT AUF 25 JAHREN SPITZEN­FORSCHUNG UND 10.000 ENTWICKLER­TAGEN UND GIBT PLANERN VOLLE KONTROLLE ÜBER DEN PLANUNGS­PROZESS.

ZUM ERSTEN MAL.

KG","title":"Founder and Managing Director"},{"date":{"end":"Present","start":"May 2021"},"description":"Erschaffe dich selbst. Ich helfe dir.

Zahlreiche Veränderungsprozesse durfte ich begleiten – auch tiefgreifende, schmerzhafte, weitreichende. Für Organisationen und Menschen überall auf der Welt.

Auch ich habe Wandel erlebt und gelernt, meine persönlichen Schatten anzunehmen. Sie sind ein Teil von mir. Meine innersten Bedürfnisse habe ich erkannt und Schutzschichten abgelegt. Diese Klarheit hilft mir, dich auf deinem Weg ein Stück zu begleiten – deinem Weg zu mehr Selbstbewusstsein und Selbstwirksamkeit.

Du lernst, dich selbst ehrlich wahrzunehmen – mit all deinen Geschichten, Herausforderungen, Sehnsüchten, Gefühlen und Gedanken. Ich spüre deine Energie und verbinde Spiritualität mit systematischem Denken und baue Brücken zwischen rationaler Geschäftswelt und intuitivem Menschsein.

Seit über 20 Jahren begleite ich den Wandel von Unternehmen auf der ganzen Welt. Darunter Audi, Australia Post, BMW, Linde, National Australia Bank, Porsche und SAP. Außerdem engagiere ich mich für Start-ups in den Bereichen Technologie, Lebensmittel und Nachhaltigkeit.

Vorwiegend begleite ich Menschen, die bereits „alles“ zu haben scheinen und als überaus erfolgreich gelten. Meist kommen Führungspersönlichkeiten zu mir, die es leid sind, sich einzig über Arbeit, Geld und Position zu definieren.

Ich bin überzeugt, dass Menschen gestalten wollen: sich selbst, ihr Leben, ihre Arbeit. Wenn wir unseren inneren Antrieb finden, leben und arbeiten wir glücklicher und erfolgreicher.

Äußere Zwänge wie Karriere, Status, Geld entfremden uns von uns selbst. Wir werden von außen motiviert, Dinge zu tun, nicht von innen. Was bleibt, ist eine Sehnsucht nach tieferem, innerem Glücklich-Sein.

Ich möchte meine Erfahrungen und Einsichten nutzen, um dir dabei zu helfen, deine Reise zu dir selbst zu beginnen, dich zu erforschen, deine persönlichen Bedürfnisse freizulegen und dein Leben in die eigenen Hände zu nehmen und zu gestalten. 

Unsere gemeinsame Mission lautet: Glücklich-Sein.","name":"CreatingCreators by Reinhard Vanhöfen","title":"Transformation Coach"}]

title: Co-Founder & CRO
summary:
🛫I co-founded amber - Europe's leading business AI - because I know how difficult it is to find internal information. This is our story:

➡️Bevor I founded amber, I had to develop various things for my work - building on existing expertise. 
In order not to always start from scratch in my old jobs, I needed to know what expertise was already available in the company. Unfortunately, there was no way to search through all the information centrally; I had to jump from data silo to data silo and search there.
This was so frustrating that sooner or later I always had to ask my colleagues for help.
The figures from various studies confirm that I was not the only one with this problem: employees spend around 30 minutes a day searching for information digitally - a number that has risen by 77% in recent years.

When the opportunity arose in 2020 for my co-founders and me to solve this problem with the help of AI, we seized the opportunity and founded amberSearch. Here's what's happened since then:

1️⃣ - 2020: 
	- Founding amber
	- Acquisition of first customers such as Ruhrkohle AG (RAG) and Siemens Energy https://ambersearch.de/referenzen/
	- Publication of first own LLM's: https://ambersearch.de/open-source/
2️⃣ - 2021: 
	- Standardisation of our solution into a product
	- Acquisition of further customers
3️⃣ - 2022: 
	- Standardisation of distribution
	- Development of various connectors to other systems
	- Growth of the team to 15 people
4️⃣ - 2023: 
	- Integration of generative AI in amberSearch in the form of amberAI so that employees can chat with their own expertise
	- Acquisition of DB Regio AG as a customer via the db mindbox, including continuation
5️⃣ - 2024:
	- developing first version of our AI-Agents
        - Increasing the number of customers to more than 100
6️⃣  - 2025:
	- Starting to heavily scale across hundrets of companies
        - Winning first international customers
7️⃣  - 2026:
	- loading...

📈A team of 50 people now works for amber and together we look after over 400 customers. 

⭐What makes amber unique?

With amber, we provide companies with a product that can be used as a standard solution and can be connected with out of the box connectors. Thanks to our own AI models, we are able to make internal expertise as quickly and easily accessible as employees know it from the internet.

Sounds exciting? Then take a look at our website now or contact me here on LinkedIn.

✅ Implement AI-powered sales automation to reduce manual tasks & increase efficiency
✅ Train sales teams to close more deals, faster
✅ Build scalable sales strategies that drive consistent pipeline growth

🔹 Why It Matters
Most sales teams waste too much time on manual processes, outdated techniques, and ineffective outreach. At Kickscale, we leverage cutting-edge sales tech and proven frameworks to help businesses increase efficiency, reduce CAC, and hit their revenue targets.

🔹 Who We Work With
🚀 B2B startups & scaleups looking to build a high-performing sales engine
📈 Sales teams aiming to improve efficiency & conversion rates
🤝 Founders & revenue leaders who want to scale predictable growth

🔹 How We Can Connect
If you’re looking to streamline your sales, implement automation, or scale faster, let’s connect. 
Always open to sharing insights, collaborating, or exploring partnerships!

💬 DM me or reach out to our team at www.kickscale.com

title: Founder & CEO
summary:
I founded Boost.space because I was tired of working with scattered, disconnected data. I knew there had to be a way to create a single source of truth.

What started as a mission to centralize data has evolved into something much bigger. We quickly realized that the next frontier isn't just organizing data for humans—it's preparing it for AI.

Powerful AI agents and automation workflows are being built every day, but they all share a common limitation: they have no memory. They execute tasks, but they don't learn from them.

That's why we're building Boost.space as the "database for AI." Our platform is the AI-Ready data layer that provides the critical long-term memory for your agents. This is the key to unlocking self-improving systems that get smarter with every action.

We're building the foundational data layer for the future of agentic AI.

If you're building in the automation and AI ecosystem, I'd love to connect and share insights.

title: Enterprise Sales Executive
summary:
I bring extensive experience as a founder, entrepreneur, and C-level executive in various digital SMEs and startups, as well as as a Director in leading system integrators.

In 1999, I founded TRIM (specializing in complex web application development for banks and enterprises), which was acquired by Capgemini in 2016, where I held the role of Engagement Director.

In 2019, I joined Thelab (an app development startup) as a partner and business developer, driving its growth and overseeing its merger with Synesthesia. At Synesthesia, I became Chief Growth Officer, focusing on business development and strengthening the organization during a period of significant expansion.

In 2023, I joined Morecognition as a shareholder and Chief Growth Officer. At the end of 2024, I joined Timeflow as an Enterprise Sales Executive.

I am highly versatile and goal-oriented, with a strong focus on problem-solving, relationship management, and driving sales in enterprise environments. My aptitude for sales and business development has consistently enabled me to deliver results and contribute to organizational success.

I aspire to create a better world and embrace new challenges to make it happen, always guided by entrepreneurial spirit, passion, fun, customer discovery, and a lean approach. I share my vision with people open to new opportunities by fostering enthusiasm and collaboration.

I have consistently invested in social and environmental projects, dedicating significant time to volunteering—particularly in educational initiatives for young people, promoting digital inclusion, and supporting those in need. I have participated in several volunteer projects in Africa and India and have founded or held leadership roles in organizations such as Informatici Senza Frontiere APS, Fondazione Lab00 ETS, LabxRivoli APS, and Club Digitale Innovazione Torino.

I also serve as a Contract Professor at the University of Turin, Department of Management.

I have over 10 years of experience in strategy, management consulting and sales with a proven track record of delivering value to clients and partners across multiple industries and geographies. I have a strong passion for innovation, technology and sports, and I am always eager to learn new skills and explore new fields. I believe that AI has the potential to transform the world of sports and create positive social impact.

Customer satisfaction, profitability, and delivering value are always at the forefront of my approach. By fostering genuine motivation and continuous development, I maximise team performance, efficiency, and effectiveness. Leading by example, I bring an entrepreneurial spirit and a "can-do" attitude to every aspect of my work. I thrive on collaboration, uniting multiple functions within the organisation to pursue a common goal.

title: Co-founder, CEO
summary:
𝗜𝗰𝗵 𝗴𝗹𝗮𝘂𝗯𝗲 𝗱𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗻, 𝗱𝗮𝘀𝘀 𝗲𝗰𝗵𝘁𝗲 𝗩𝗲𝗿ä𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗿𝘂𝗻𝗴 𝗱𝗼𝗿𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗴𝗶𝗻𝗻𝘁, 𝘄𝗼 𝘄𝗶𝗿 𝗮𝘂𝗳𝗵ö𝗿𝗲𝗻, 𝗻𝘂𝗿 𝘇𝘂 𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗴𝗶𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻 – 𝘂𝗻𝗱 𝗲𝗻𝗱𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗵 𝗮𝗻𝗳𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗻, 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗮𝗸𝘁𝗶𝘃 𝘇𝘂 𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗱𝗲𝗹𝗻.

Als jemand, der selbst über 10 Jahre in einem klassischen mittelständischen Maschinenbauunternehmen gearbeitet hat, weiß ich, wie frustrierend es sein kann, wenn ein winziges Teil fehlt und plötzlich alles zum Stillstand kommt. 

Zeit ist hier ja wortwörtlich Geld. 

Deshalb habe ich beschlossen, die Sache selbst in die Hand zu nehmen und diesen Teufelskreis zu durchbrechen. Und unzähligen Maschinenbauern dabei zu helfen, das riesige Potenzial des Ersatzteilgeschäfts im After-Sales endlich als gewinnbringenden Wettbewerbsvorteil zu nutzen!

Mit meinem Co-Founder Fabian Gemmecke haben wir PartsCloud gegründet. Unsere Softwarelösung PartsOS Planning ermöglicht es OEMs, ihre Ersatzteilplanung endlich vorausschauend zu steuern - mit KI und Machine Learning statt Bauchgefühl. Mit präzisen Prognosen und datengestützten Einblicken stellt PartsOS Planning sicher, dass Ersatzteile zur richtigen Zeit verfügbar sind. Fehlbestände werden reduziert, Überbestände minimiert, Kosten gesenkt und unzufriedene Kunden endlich der Vergangenheit an.

𝗦𝘁𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗱𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗻:
- Ersatzteile vor Ort, bevor sie gebraucht werden
- Vorausschauender Service statt ständiger Feuerwehreinsätze
- Besserer Kundenservice, der dich vom Wettbewerb abhebt

Es liegt an uns allen, den Maschinenbau, Deutschlands zweitgrößte Branche, mit smarten digitalen Lösungen fit für die Zukunft zu machen. Geht nicht, gibts nicht.

title: CEO & Co-Founder
summary:
I am a purpose-driven serial entrepreneur passionate about creating solutions that change the world. From pioneering advancements in Life Sciences to improve patient outcomes, I am now stepping into Material Science to revolutionize the field with cutting-edge innovations.

With over 20 years of experience across industries and geographies, I have led ventures from inception to successful exits, including founding a company acquired by a leading Nordic IT player. My background spans entrepreneurship, executive leadership, commercialization, business development, angel investing, and VC LP roles equipping me with a holistic perspective on driving transformative growth.

I thrive on collaboration with visionary individuals and believe that good karma is the foundation for building long-term, impactful relationships. Rooted in my multicultural heritage as a Danish-born individual with Indian roots, I aim to bridge innovation and humanity in every endeavor. 

Let's change the world - for the better!
titleDescription:
We are PhaseTree  -  a deep-tech start-up spun out of the Technical University of Denmark. At PhaseTree, we’re driven by a singular mission: to accelerate the green transition through cutting-edge technology.

The green transition is heavily reliant on the development of advanced materials. However the materials discovery process today faces immense challenges as developing these materials is both extremely costly and time-consuming. 

These hurdles delay the development of sustainable technologies and thereby delay a greener future.

Our solution at PhaseTree is transformative. We combine advanced computer simulation with lab automation using a science first and AI on top approach to accelerate the discovery of sustainable advanced materials. By reducing R&D time and costs, we empower industries and researchers to create solutions that drive the green transition—faster and more efficiently using our platform.

Our team brings a unique combination of expertise. We are a group of founders and advisors that are building a company that bridges science, technology, business and impact. 

Together, let’s innovate for a sustainable future—one material at a time

Forward, Always

title: Founder & CEO
summary:
Tras más de 15 años liderando proyectos en banca y sector farmacéutico, vi de cerca cómo el cumplimiento normativo se gestionaba con herramientas obsoletas.

En 2019 fundé icloudCompliance®, un SaaS que digitaliza y automatiza el cumplimiento legal, la sostenibilidad (ESG), la calidad y los sistemas de gestión (GRC). Nuestra tecnología —basada en inteligencia artificial y blockchain— permite a cientos de empresas cumplir con normativas como la ISO 27001, RGPD, canal de denuncias o la CSRD, sin morir en el intento.

Hoy ayudamos a más de 400 empresas en 35 países, con 120.000 usuarios que gestionan sus riesgos de forma simple, trazable y segura.

Soy auditor certificado ISO 27001, Delegado de Protección de Datos (DPO), experto en compliance penal y promotor de una visión: hacer que el cumplimiento normativo deje de ser una carga, y se convierta en un factor competitivo.

Creo en equipos autónomos, entornos de confianza y tecnología como palanca para construir empresas éticas, sostenibles y resilientes.

¿Tu empresa también quiere avanzar en cumplimiento normativo y sostenibilidad sin fricción?
Estoy a un mensaje de distancia.

title: Chief Executive Officer
summary:
Justin Pike is founder and CEO of Burbank Developments - creators of CPoI, the world’s first technology that enables card-present payments to be accepted in online channels. This cutting-edge technology works within the existing standards over well established and globally resilient rails to enable consumers to tap their cards and enter their PIN securely on their own mobile devices at checkout. It mimics the in-store checkout - a user experience that is universally accessible, inclusive, familiar, and trusted by consumers across all demographics globally. 

 

As an innovator in the IT industry for over 27  years, Justin has founded numerous successful companies including eNett - a multi-billion-dollar payment processor and the world’s largest processor for the travel industry, and MYPINPAD, which invented PIN on Mobile technology and grew to be the world’s leading SoftPOS provider. 

 

Justin’s vision for Burbank, and indeed all the companies he has founded has always been to make payments safe, simple, and secure for everyone. He has built some of the world’s most complex payment and security solutions that continue to be used today.  Justin’s lens has always been first and foremost on ease of use, accessibility, and security for the consumer, but also with a view to deliver overwhelming revenue uplift and risk reduction to merchants who are most exposed. 

 

Under Justin’s hand, some of the world’s most transformative payments, identity and authentication solutions have been created and delivered. A passionate innovator in this field – nobody knows this space better

title: Vice President Sales
summary:
I help organizations turn enterprise complexity into clear decisions and scalable go-to-market execution.

Enterprise sales today isn’t about better pitching; instead it’s about orchestrating decision-making across functions, translating operational complexity into value, and building GTM engines that hold up under pressure.

Over the last years, I’ve led and scaled sales teams in data-driven, low-digital and high-stakes environments most recently across European grocery retail, manufacturing and supply chains.

What I do in practice:
- turn complex operational problems into clear, defensible business cases
- navigate political buying centers across Ops, IT, Finance & Commercial
- coach AEs to run high-impact, consultative enterprise conversations
- design GTM motions that work where theory breaks and reality starts
- build sales orgs that stay effective as complexity increases

My style:
Hands-on. Analytical. Calm under pressure. I don’t push deals. I help teams see the decision landscape clearly and act with confidence inside it.

Today, as VP Sales at Freshflow, I’m responsible for scaling the commercial motion across Europe in a category-defining AI environment.
Translating product value into repeatable, sustainable revenue across fresh food retail.

I’m especially interested in conversations around:
- scaling consultative sales in complex industries
- enterprise GTM design & execution
- coaching senior sellers and frontline leaders
- navigating growth when deals get political, slow and messy

Let’s connect if you’re:
🔹 Leading or scaling a B2B Sales or GTM organization
🔹 Selling into complex, multi-stakeholder environments
🔹 Operating in data-heavy, operationally critical industries

#SalesLeadership #EnterpriseSales #ConsultativeSelling #GTMStrategy #SalesCoaching

titleDescription:
LiveDrop provides solutions for secure, unidirectional and offline data transfers, protecting your critical data and systems.

The patented LiveDrop protocol uses any display as the "sender" and any camera as the "receiver" and can be thought of as a virtual data diode. LiveDrop's solutions work x-platform on Windows, Linux, iOS and Android. 

After years of technology development, the first version of LiveDrop was launched at CES Las Vegas in January 2024. 

Currently available is the free LiveDrop Offline Sharing app, a software suite for Windows and an SDK to implement the protocol itself within existing or new applications.

LiveDrop is funded by SecFund, established by the Netherlands Ministry of Defense.

Tremau is a Paris-based technology start-up from the Trust&Safety industry focused on developing innovative tools to assist actors across the digital industry mitigate their regulatory and operational risks.

At Tremau we are convinced that the digital revolution is a fundamental force for good. But we are also aware of the challenges this revolution brings to our societies and of the mounting pressure regulators are imposing on businesses to limit their potential negative externalities.

Our ambition is to support the safe and responsible use of technology by providing online service providers and users of AI-enabled technologies with cost-effective and easily implementable tools to comply with upcoming regulations, in a way that is transparent and respectful of fundamental freedoms.

title: Co-Founder and COO
summary:
Today, the online space has a fundamental influence on all aspects of our lives including on what we buy, who we vote for or how we raise our children. With all the opportunities and freedom comes also the responsibility of engaging with online spaces where people, especially young users, can engage safely while businesses grow sustainably. As platforms grow, so do challenges like harmful content, misinformation, and online abuse. Ignoring these issues isn’t an option; it puts users at risk and damages reputations.

At Tremau, we help companies stay ahead of risks, meet compliance, and build trust with their users. The real value? Safer communities, stronger brands, and long-term success. In today’s digital world, trust isn’t just nice to have, it’s a competitive edge.

title: CEO & Co-Founder
summary:
I'm Robbert Lodewijks, CEO and co-founder of HULO.ai. I grew up in a village in the north of the Netherlands, where a close-knit community and strong values shaped who I am. With a background in mechanical engineering and business administration, I’ve always been driven by curiosity, how things work, how systems connect, and how people thrive when given trust and responsibility.

Living in Taiwan during my studies opened my eyes to nature, but also global inequalities, especially around basic needs. That experience sparked a deeper purpose: I wanted to spend my time building something meaningful. In 2021, I co-founded HULO with my co-founders Frank and Rudy as a spin-off company focused on one of the world’s most pressing challenges—reducing water loss and ensuring access to safe, reliable drinking water. Because yes, 30% of all drinking water is lost globally... 

At HULO, we’re revolutionizing how water networks are monitored, using data and AI to detect leaks and inefficiencies before they become critical. My vision is that one day, I’ll be able to tell my grandchildren how we helped improve lives around the world by making clean water truly abundant.

I’m a go-getter at heart—honest, ambitious, and people-focused. I believe in leading by trusting others, creating space for growth, and building strong teams that move fast with purpose. Above all, I’m a family man inspired by making a lasting, positive impact.

Contact details:
M: robbert@hulo.ai
T: +31611500396
titleDescription:
save time. save water. 

Globally, 30% of clean drinking water is lost to leaks. At HULO, we aim to ensure every drop counts by integrating AI with physics-based models to detect and localize leaks quickly, seamlessly integrating with existing systems without heavy hardware investments.

Our core values—honesty, adventure, achievement, and respect—fuel our mission to revolutionize water management, promoting transparency and sustainable practices that support global conservation efforts.

Besides aiding utilities, HULO helps corporates meet their water sustainability goals through precise volumetric benefit accounting, conserving water and assisting partners in achieving environmental targets, enhancing global water management.

title: Co-Founder - CRO
summary:
Lorenzo Barbantini Scanni is a seasoned entrepreneur, angel investor, and advisor with over 20 years of experience driving innovation and supporting the global startup ecosystem. In 2021, he co-founded Colossus, a regulated custodian and blockchain infrastructure provider. At Colossus, Lorenzo spearheaded the creation of the Institutional Hub, launched in 2023, a groundbreaking platform designed to bridge institutional custodians with blockchain validators. The Institutional Hub enables secure large-scale staking, governance, and seamless interaction across 24 blockchains, providing institutions with a compliant, efficient, and scalable solution to engage with decentralized networks.

A crypto pioneer since 2014, Lorenzo’s work in blockchain is complemented by his entrepreneurial achievements. In 2014, he co-founded Stamplay, a low-code development platform acquired by Apple in 2019, and in 2012, he co-founded Pick1, a data-driven insights platform acquired by Events.com in 2016. Earlier in his career, he played a key role in the exit of Xaltia to Eng.it, part of Engineering Ingegneria Informatica, in 2008.

Beyond his ventures, Lorenzo is deeply involved in empowering startups as an angel investor and advisor. He has worked with LUISS ENLABS, InnovAction, and Startup Bootcamp, mentoring early-stage startups in strategy, scaling, and fundraising. His career reflects a unique blend of entrepreneurial success, investment expertise, and a commitment to fostering the next generation of innovators.
titleDescription:

The Institutional Hub by Colossus is a revolutionary B2B marketplace that connects custodians and their clients—like asset managers, banks, and VCs—to a network of validators, enabling secure staking and governance directly from custody. Our unique business model is performance-driven, requiring only a fee on validator staking rewards, making it a cost-effective and scalable solution for institutions looking to maximise their digital asset potential
Come find out more on https://colossus.digital/

title: Head of Sales & Partnership, South Europe (fractional)
summary:
I am an advisor and consultancy partner in the fields of sustainable procurement & supply chain decarbonization.

My collaborative approach has enabled the successful rollout of global sustainable procurement programs, recognized by the industry through multiple accolades, including a shortlist for CPO of the year. Equipped with key certifications such as Master Black Belt, I am committed to refining manufacturing processes and championing ESG principles across European markets.

My clients include climate tech start-ups & investors, large corporations in energy-intensive industries & leading consulting firms. 

After obtaining an engineering degree from one of France’s leading technical “Grandes Ecoles” and a Management degree from Duke, I gained my domain expertise by working up the corporate ladder in large multinationals and PE-owned companies, while engaging in entrepreneurial ventures on the side.

Contact me to talk about sustainability, decarbonizing supply chains, scope 3 baselining & reduction, future of procurement or re-inventing organizations.

title: Strategic Partner & Business Development
summary:
I build and scale AI-driven companies that turn complex risk and knowledge challenges into measurable business outcomes.

For 30+ years, I’ve introduced and grown innovative technology companies across EMEA - taking breakthrough solutions from early-stage entry to commercial scale, multimillion revenues, M&A, and IPO contribution.

My focus today:
- Technology that drives sustainability. Tech for good.
- AI that changes behaviour.
- AI that reduces risk.
- AI that delivers measurable ROI.
- AI that helps people getting the job done.

Because the real opportunity in AI is not automation alone - it’s behaviour change at scale.

Founder – Ailuna
======================
Habits with impact. Action drives belief.
Ailuna is a gamified behaviour-change platform focused on sustainability, fraud prevention, and cybersecurity.

We help organizations embed positive daily habits that protect employees, customers, and consumers — while improving measurable business outcomes.

Less awareness.
More action.
Trackable impact.

Custom programs turn ESG, cyber resilience, and fraud prevention into scalable, data-driven behaviour change.

Strategic Advisor – Talvi
======================
Talvi unlocks the value in existing L&D content.

Using AI, employees can ask questions and receive precise answers in the moment of need — transforming static content into an interactive knowledge layer.

Higher productivity. Better retention. Stronger ROI on existing investments.

Strategic Advisor – InsureVision
======================
InsureVision applies AI video analytics to reduce fleet risk and lower insurance costs.

The platform analyzes forward-facing dashcam footage and surfaces only safety-critical events — no new hardware and no in-cabin cameras required.

Clear commercial value. Immediate ROI.

Endurance Mindset
======================
I’ve completed 12 × Ironman races — including Norseman Xtreme Triathlon — as well as Marathon des Sables (250 km), Cape Wrath Ultra (400 km), and long-distance ski races such as Vasaloppet and Birkebeinerrennet.

Long horizon thinking.
Disciplined execution.
Resilience under pressure.

I live by the Ironman mantra: Anything is possible.

If you’re building, investing in, or partnering around AI that drives real-world impact — let’s connect.

title: VP of Marketing
summary:
I believe marketing is both science and storytelling. My career started 15+ years ago, learning from the likes of Neil Patel, Moz Academy and many skillfull colleagues along the way, working across corporations large and small, and later building my own businesses. Today, as VP of Marketing at OpusFlow, I’m on a mission to turn us into the #1 ERP for sustainable installation companies.

I know what it takes to build something from nothing. With my husband and business partner Lee, I co-founded My360Tours.com — spotting a gap in real estate software and creating one of the most recognized virtual tour platforms used by thousands worldwide. Alongside that, we grew My360 Web Solutions into a thriving agency with 30+ international clients and a strong team of 9+ in Spain.

As a leader, my principle is simple: bring out the best in people. If you’ve got talent, I’ll push you to master it. I reward hard work, expect focus, and protect my team fiercely. People call me fair but consistent. My strengths lie in project management, budget control, and creative content, but my true skill is building high-performing, empowered teams. (And squeezing suppliers for every penny I can get!) 

At OpusFlow, I’m tackling a challenge that drives me mad: too many sustainable installation companies still rely on spreadsheets. We’re showing them how smart ERP can transform a mediocre business into a profitable, growing one in months. And with every company we help, we’re pushing the world toward a more sustainable future.

Achievements I’m proud of:

* Scaling My360Tours to global recognition & search engine dominance

* Growing My360 Web Solutions into an international agency

* Creating a life in Spain where business, family, and sunshine go hand in hand

Outside of work, you’ll find me hiking, exploring Spanish villages, enjoying tapas, or learning to play golf (jury’s still out).

🚀 Let’s connect if you’re building in SaaS, sustainability, or simply want to share a good story.

summary:
Dynamic and goal-oriented, serial entrepreneur, with strong leadership skills. 20 years international experience in tech startups, scale-ups and large organisations. Involved in several exits. Held senior leadership roles in sales, marketing, product management and business development, with consistent success in driving growth and over-achieving on revenue targets. 

Advisor at Kaylo, DN Capital. Founder of non-profit children’s entrepreneurial education Bizworld UK, and Member of London Revenue Collective - now Pavillion.

- Previously CRO at everyLIFE, a health tech Scaleup company leading the way in digital care management for homecare, reablement and residential care.

- Previously CRO leading Sales and Marketing at Soma Analytics, a digital mental Health Startup, providing businesses and individuals with the smart way to beat stress at work. Soma was acquired by Prenetics.

- Head of Sales EMEA  General Business at Xactly Corporation, SaaS platform for incentive compensation and leading Salesforce partner.  Nasdaq IPO and subsequent acquisition by Vista Equity Partners.

- 14 years+ Europe, HQ US/Silicon Valley, and Latin America with Oracle Corporation: Leadership roles in Enterprise Sales, Business Development, Marketing and Technical Consulting for Middleware Solutions, Data Analytics, Big Data and Enterprise Applications.

- Silicon Valley Startup Niku: Head of Product Management for their Enterprise Applications (now Computer Associates). Nasdaq IPO and subsequent acquisition

- Scandinavian Startup Interse: VP of Product Management Content Management and Search platform (backed by largest Scandinavian VC Nordic Venture Partners). Member of Executive Management Team.


Passionate about philanthropy, wellbeing, technology and education.

title: Co-Founder
summary:
I am an investor-turned-entrepreneur having spent over a decade as an investment professional doing deals in private equity.

Currently, I am a Co-Founder and COO of Dealstack, a "private equity tech" platform designed to revolutionise deal administration for private equity professionals and lawyers.

I helped found Dealstack to address a problem I experienced first hand during my time in private equity: the inefficiencies caused by repetitive administrative tasks that slowed down deal-making and value creation across the organisation.

At Dealstack, we’re streamlining common private equity workflows so that investment professionals and legal teams can focus on what matters to drive returns, not get bogged down by deal admin.

I am convinced that private equity will change a lot in the next years and my focus is on helping deliver this transition. We know that for change to happen you need to deliver efficiency, precision, and value - these are core principles for us at Dealstack.

summary:
In my current role, I lead startup initiatives at Bsure, a company dedicated to helping other businesses optimize Microsoft 365 license costs, gain insights into their users, leading to reduced expenses, enhanced security, and improved data quality.

After a decade of experience in the finance sector, driven by a passion for boosting profitability, I came to the realization that managing subscription costs can be challenging for companies, as these expenses are often considered necessities. Collaborating with my co-founders, we recognized that the challenge of effectively managing Microsoft 365 subscriptions and users is no different from the broader subscription management landscape due to a lack of insight, resulting in companies paying a significant premium—often as much as 20% more than necessary—for their Microsoft 365 licenses. Bsure was founded to provide companies with the essential tool they require to make informed decisions based on their own data.

title: Founder
summary:
Accountants are drowning in work they can't hire for. The bookkeeping talent pipeline collapsed years ago, and AI that just "automates transactions" doesn't solve the real problem: 40-60% of transactions need human judgment—context that lives in emails, Slack threads, and the accountant's head.

I'm building Jenesys to capture that context and teach AI how problems actually get resolved. We've built the learning loop: a comms hub that captures query resolution, a headless reviewer that learns from corrections, and client rules that compound over time. The result is dedicated-bookkeeper accuracy at fractional cost—memory that scales.

Before this, I spent a decade in enterprise SaaS taking B2B service lines from first revenue to £8m ARR across FinTech, Telco, and AI. Earlier, I architected digital transformation programmes for insurance, banking and government IT services at Spark New Zealand. I started as a founder in 1998, exited in 2006, and came back to building in 2018.

What drives me: AI infrastructure that makes small businesses fundable by giving them numbers they can trust.
titleDescription:
Accounting practices can't hire enough bookkeepers, and the ones they have are stretched across 30-80 clients - too many to remember the context each business needs for accurate numbers.

We're building AI that learns bookkeeping the way humans do: from corrections and context. Our platform captures how accountants and clients actually resolve queries and then trains AI to apply that judgment at scale. 

The result is dedicated-bookkeeper accuracy without the headcount, compressing month-end from 30 days to 48 hours.

title: Founding Team | Head of Sales
summary:
Te cuento un secreto: nunca he hecho una entrevista de trabajo. No porque sea un genio, sino porque el sector del automóvil me encontró antes de que pudiera buscar otra cosa. Con 19 años ya estaba vendiendo coches, y desde entonces no he parado.

Estudié Administración y Finanzas, pero donde realmente he aprendido ha sido trabajando, equivocándome, liderando equipos y cerrando operaciones en el día a día. He vivido de todo: momentos buenos, malos y otros en los que tocaba simplemente aguantar. Más de 1.500 coches vendidos, mil conversaciones, mil historias… y sobre todo, muchas lecciones. Aprendí a liderar, a mover equipos, a adaptarme rápido y a tomar decisiones bajo presión. Nunca estudié ventas ni liderazgo, pero siempre me han salido de forma natural.

He pasado por todos los modelos posibles: el B2C de mostrador de toda la vida, el B2B con empresas y profesionales, y ahora estoy en el mundo SaaS, donde las reglas son otras, pero la esencia es la misma. Ese recorrido me ha dado una visión muy completa de cómo se vende, cómo se trabaja en equipo y cómo se construye algo desde cero.

Y lo que cambió todo fue conocer, casi por casualidad, a Dealcar cuando todavía era una idea. Tenía una vida estable, con mi rutina, un buen sueldo y todo en orden… pero decidí dar el salto. Dejé esa seguridad para apostar por un proyecto/sueño que conecta de lleno con mi historia y con lo que creo que el sector necesita. Pasé de un entorno tradicional a uno 100% digital, y eso me obligó a aprender, desaprender y volver a construir.

Vengo del barro. De escuchar al cliente en persona, de cerrar ventas a pulso, de pelear cada oportunidad. Y por más que avance la tecnología, siempre voy a estar cerca de esa realidad. Porque es lo que me ha formado y lo que me sigue dando perspectiva cada día.

Me gusta la gente que trabaja, que no se cree más que nadie y que sabe de dónde viene. Al final, eso es lo que intento ser cada día: alguien comprometido, con los pies en el suelo, y con ganas de seguir aprendiendo.
titleDescription:
Me incorporé al proyecto como primer comercial en una fase muy temprana, cuando todavía estábamos validando el producto y entendiendo bien las necesidades del sector. Empezamos con un enfoque 100% en field sales: visitar concesionarios, escuchar, probar y ajustar el mensaje. Esa experiencia nos sirvió para construir desde cero un sistema comercial propio, basado en lo que realmente funciona sobre el terreno.

Con el tiempo hemos evolucionado hacia un modelo más digital, combinando estrategias de field sales con online sales. Hoy lidero un equipo de 4 personas con enfoque full cycle: desde prospección hasta cierre y activación, siempre con cercanía y compromiso con los concesionarios.

Mi día a día:

- Vender, vender, vender...

- Coordinar el equipo comercial y trabajar codo a codo con ellos

- Diseñar, probar y mejorar el playbook de ventas

- Acompañar a concesionarios en su digitalización, desde la demo hasta su crecimiento real

- Colaborar con producto para traducir lo que pasa en la calle en soluciones útiles

summary:
Hi, I'm Tamara, welcome to my profile...

My journey into the world of e-mobility started with a degree in economics, where I focused on sustainability and how innovation shapes economies. I carried that focus into my early career at HERE Technologies, where I discovered a deep interest in solving the real-world challenges of sustainable mobility.

Since then, I’ve built up over seven years of experience in the mobility and tech space. Fom commercial roles in sales and partnerships to launching products and crafting go-to-market strategies that make complex technologies feel simple and useful. 

At Cariqa, we're building the first end-to-end billing and pricing platform for EV charging – designed to give charge point operators full control, streamline operations, and make pricing more transparent and consistent across all channels. In my role as CCO I get to combine all of that: working hands-on with charge point operators, scaling our platform across Europe, and challenging the outdated status quo in EV charging.

I believe that if we want EVs to be the default way of getting around, we need to make charging just as intuitive as driving :))…

titleDescription:
What is Introw PRM?
🚀 Revolutionize Your Partner Relationships 🤝

Introw is a cutting-edge Partner Relationship Management (PRM) platform designed to streamline and enhance your collaborations with B2B partners. 

By seamlessly integrating with your existing CRM system, Introw ensures your CRM remains the single source of truth, allowing you to set up a personalized partner portal in minutes—no coding required. 

Key Features:
✅ Quick Implementation: Deploy your partner portal in minutes - instead of months
✅ CRM Integration at the core: Keep your CRM as the single source of truth - automatically syncing partner data, deals, support cases & any custom object. 
✅ Automate Commissions: Create plans, give partners visibility & manage pay-outs.
✅ Automated Partner Engagement: Automate updates based on CRM data, share product news, and engage partners directly—no portal login required. 
✅ Comprehensive Partner Management: Organize your partnerships by applying tiers, such as Gold, Silver, and Bronze, and manage commissions effectively. 
✅ Content Sharing and Enablement: Share content and resources with partners, including videos, documents, and real-time CRM components. 
✅  Form builder: Create forms 2-way integrated with your CRM to automate deal/lead registration flows - automating partner attribution. 

Join over 300 companies that trust Introw to increase partnership revenue & engagement.  Experience a PRM solution that is simple to use, effective, and keeps everyone on the same page. 

Get Started Today!🎉
Launch your free partner portal or request a demo to see how Introw can transform your partner relationships and drive revenue on autopilot.

title: Chief Executive Officer
summary:
I'm CEO of Kneu Health, a University of Oxford spinout on a mission to transform care for people with Parkinson’s and dementia. We’ve recently achieved a major milestone — FDA 510(k) clearance for our smartphone-based digital platform — bringing us one step closer to making neurological care radically more accessible and scalable.

I have a proven track record in building and leading high-impact healthtech businesses, securing multi-million-pound investments, navigating complex regulatory pathways, and delivering commercial growth in mission-driven environments.

Previously, I was Entrepreneur in Residence at Oxford Science Enterprises and CEO of Health Data Research UK (HDRUK), the UK’s national institute for health data science, where I led national strategy and cross-sector innovation to harness data for patient benefit.

Before that, I was a Director at 2020 Delivery (now The PSC), advising NHS trusts, universities, and central government on strategy, transformation, and delivery. I began my career as a Chartered Engineer at ICI, followed by roles at McKinsey & Company.

I hold an MBA from Harvard Business School and MA/MEng from the University of Cambridge. I’m passionate about scaling data-led innovation, building exceptional teams, and improving lives through technology.

summary:
Dave Sutter is an experienced entrepreneur, executive, builder, and expert in the area of blockchain and crypto technologies and their application in mainstream financial services. He is a veteran of the industry who has pioneered the technology's application in financial services, specifically in asset tokenization, stablecoins, and transaction banking. 

Over his career, Dave has worked with many of the world’s leading financial institutions, technology providers, corporations, industry bodies, and governmental agencies from around the globe on designing, building, and scaling market-leading software platforms for financial services. He has deep connections in both financial services, banking, and the blockchain industry, being one of the first people in the blockchain space to abstract away the core technology behind cryptocurrencies and begin applying the technology to mainstream financial services like payments and global trade.  He is world renowned thought-leader and has spoken at events around the world. 

Dave is a graduate of Washington University in St. Louis and currently resides in London UK.

title: Head of Sales
summary:
"Hope is not a strategy. Data & AI are."

In complex B2B sales, success is not a coincidence—it is the result of a clear methodology. To me, selling means communicating the business value of a solution so precisely that closing a deal becomes the logical consequence of structured decisions, rather than the product of gut feeling or hope.

I have spent over 25 years perfecting this standard of operational excellence in tech sales. As a graduate in Media Informatics and a former founder with a successful exit, I know the entire journey: from the first line of code and achieving market leadership to selling my own company to a global corporation. Today, I combine this entrepreneurial foundation with deep expertise in Data Management, Analytics, and AI to make companies precisely steerable.

Expertise in Data-Driven Strategic Steering

I know that AI in B2B sales is only as valuable as the data foundation it operates on. My focus, therefore, lies on the strategic architecture:

Data Management & Quality: I know how to structure data sources and ensure data quality, so that information is not just present but serves as a reliable basis for executive decisions.

AI & Analytics: I understand how to deploy AI models and analytics tools to identify patterns in complex markets, objectively validate forecasts, and make the business value of a pipeline mathematically resilient.

Dual Role as Strategist and Mentor

🚀 In Operational Leadership: I know the levers required to transform sales processes from a "black box" into a reliable steering instrument for management. My focus is on architecting go-to-market models that make growth predictable—based on data validation rather than mere assumptions.

💡 As a Sparring Partner for Tech & AI Startups: I guide founding teams in establishing their market and sales strategies on a solid foundation from day one. I know the pitfalls of scaling and understand how to structure deals and build forecasts that stand up to the scrutiny of investors and decision-makers.

My goal remains constant: turning vague opportunities into reliable results—through technological intelligence, clear structures, and a consistent alignment with measurable business value.

Als ehrenamtlicher Mentor im CyberForum teile ich meine 25+ Jahre B2B-Vertriebserfahrung mit Tech-Startups und zeige ihnen, worauf es wirklich ankommt.

Meine eigene Gründererfahrung hat mich gelehrt: Vertrieb sollte die oberste Priorität eines Startup-Gründers sein! Zu viele Startups scheitern an typischen Vertriebsfehlern wie:

- Unzureichendes Vertriebs-Know-how
- Mangelhaftes Pipeline-Management und Opportunity-Bewertung
- Fehlendes Verständnis für Kunden, ihren Bedarf und ihre Kaufgewohnheiten

Im Mentoring zeige ich, was unter der Motorhaube erfolgreichen B2B-Vertriebs passiert:
- Wie man einen skalierbaren Vertrieb von Grund auf richtig aufbaut
- Wie man echte Kundenbedarfe erkennt (Hint: Der offensichtliche Grund ist selten das wahre Kaufmotiv)
- Wie man sich im Dschungel des B2B-Buying Centers zurechtfindet
- Welche Erfolgsfaktoren nötig sind, um Deals zu gewinnen, woran man scheitern kann, und wie die ungeschriebenen Regeln des Vertriebs lauten

Meine Motivation: Tech-Startups von Anfang an vertrieblich stark aufstellen - denn nur wer seine Vertriebsprozesse, Opportunity-Bewertung und Kundenbedarfsanalyse beherrscht, schafft die Basis für nachhaltiges Wachstum.","name":"CyberForum","title":"Startup Mentoring B2B-Vertrieb"},{"date":{"end":"Jun 2025","start":"Mar 2024"},"description":"Als VP Strategic Alliances sehe ich meine Aufgabe darin, Brücken zu bauen – zwischen Technologieanbietern, Märkten und Partnern.

Durch meine langjährige Erfahrung im B2B-Vertrieb verstehe ich, wie Märkte ticken, welche Dynamiken Wachstum treiben und welche Hürden Kooperationen scheitern lassen. title: VP of Growth & Marketing
summary:
I'm Ivana, and I help health companies turn traction into repeatable, scalable growth and launch new markets.

My career has taken me on many adventures across Europe, Asia, and U.S.: I’ve built global teams, scaled operations, led go-to-market, and advised companies on community-led growth.

Today, I’m VP of Growth and Marketing at OpenHealth Technologies, where we’re fixing one of healthcare’s biggest challenges: making lab data usable. Although 70% of health decisions rely on it, most of it remains fragmented and untapped. Our platform fixes that by transforming reports from any source into structured, AI-ready data and historical insights. We’re trusted by leading health and longevity organizations worldwide, including Roche, Aware and SmartFit. 

This work is deeply personal! After years of navigating my own health journey and challenges, I shifted my energy toward helping build a future where healthcare is proactive and personalized. 

Prior to this, I was part of the founding team at Social+, the platform powering in-app social networks for brands like Noom, Airbnb, Harley-Davidson, and Grupo Boticário. I also led Southeast Asia expansion for Thailand’s first fintech unicorn’s e-wallet ($4B TPV, backed by Alipay), and set up sourcing operations in rural China for an e-commerce startup (acquired).
titleDescription:

With $4M in venture funding and hubs in Germany, the Netherlands, and Brazil, we serve clients globally. Healthtech, wellness, and supplementation companies embed our API to launch new products and get access to AI-ready data while saving significant development resources. Clinics, laboratories, insurers, pharma, and longevity providers use our platform to deliver personalized care, reduce operational burdens, and engage patients.

That’s where I learned to navigate complexity with confidence: recognizing patterns, anticipating shifts and shaping strategies that blend vision with execution.

My work is grounded in a simple belief: organizations change only when the people who lead them evolve.

My perspective is shaped by three anchors: energy, clarity, and trust in human potential.
I love teams that dare, take ownership and collaborate to build what did not exist before.

I bring structure where direction is needed, creativity where space is missing and a constant focus on tangible impact.

I believe in global cross-pollination, responsible innovation and partnerships that generate not only results but culture.

Across everything I do, I carry one ambition: to create spaces where talent activates, ideas turn into action and people feel part of something that evolves.

That’s what moves me.
